HEADWORD: Attenuant
<hw>At*ten"u*ant</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>attenuans</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>attenuare</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>att⟦eacute⟧nuant</ets>. See <er>Attenuate</er>.]</ety> <def>Making
thin, as fluids; diluting; rendering less dense and viscid;
diluent.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A medicine
that thins or dilutes the fluids; a diluent.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Attenuate</ent>⟦br⟧
